Package software.leonov.common.collect

Interface Sortedlist<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements held in this sorted-list
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, SortedCollection<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Skiplist, Treelist
    public interface Sortedlist<E>
extends SortedCollection<E>
    A SortedCollection which may contain duplicate elements and allows users to access or remove elements by their integer index.

    This is the list analog of sorted set.

    Author:
    Zhenya Leonov

      • sublist

        Sortedlist<E> sublist​(int fromIndex,
                      int toIndex)
        Returns a view of the portion of this sorted-list whose elements range between fromIndex, inclusive, and toIndex, exclusive. If fromIndex and toIndex are equal, the returned sorted-list is empty. The returned sorted-list is backed by this sorted-list, so changes in the returned sorted-list are reflected in this sorted-list, and vice-versa.

        The returned sorted-list will throw an IllegalArgumentException on an attempt to insert an element outside its range.

        Parameters:
        fromIndex - low endpoint (inclusive) of the returned sorted-list
        toIndex - high endpoint (exclusive) of the returned sorted-list
        Returns:
        a view of the portion of this sorted-list within the specified range
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if fromIndex < 0 || toIndex > size || fromIndex > toIndex

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()
        Returns the hash code value for this sorted-list. The hash code of a sorted-list is defined to be the result of the following calculation: 
         int hashCode = 1;
 for (E e : this)
     hashCode = 31 * hashCode + (e == null ? 0 : e.hashCode());
